            . I am a <rs id="t17680907-42-viclabel233" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680907-42-victim447 t17680907-42-viclabel233"></join>, one of the prisoners is a plumber, the other a plumber's labourer, they were laying a flat for me at a building I was about; I happened to hear one say to the other, that piece is safe enough; I looked about, and found a piece of new sheet-lead under the stairs hid, I set 
               <persName id="t17680907-42-person449">
                  George 
                  Duke 
               <interp inst="t17680907-42-person449" type="surname" value="Duke"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-42-person449" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680907-42-person449" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             to watch it; after a time it was gone unknown to him, the prisoners were still at work; by looking about, I found it in the servants hall concealed; we searched farther, and in the house-keeper's room we found where their clothes were lying, another piece of lead concealed behind some slates, we let all lie; when the prisoners went to go to dinner at one, we let them go out; after which I went and stopped them, Goodwin the plumber had a piece weighing 41 pounds, between his shirt and his waistcoat, doubled up, and a smaller piece in his coat pocket; and Manning, he had a piece concealed in the same manner; I made them carry the lead, as they had concealed it under their waistcoats, before Justice Spinnage, there it was taken out, it was all new sheet lead (produced and deposed to.)</p>
